In this part of the codebase we have IO classes, meant to load static data for the game engine that is constant and singular at run-time. A city may have a bit array to indicate which buildings have been built there, but when we need to figure our the cost and effect of any given building, we map the index of the bit in our building bit array to a static list of buildings costs and effects. There are many IO modules, most look very much similar. Testing here is done by just loading and printing the data. 

The data we load in these modules typically include prerequisites for any given data entry. These prerequisites come in different types. We usually have a single tech requirement, followed by 4 optional requirements of variable. As an example, a building will require a tech and may additionally require some other building, a resource, or some general state flag to be build. 
